HEADWORD: Tacet
<hw>Ta"cet</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. impers.</pos> <ety>[L., it is
silent, 3d pers.pr. of <ets>tacere</ets> to be silent.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>It is silent; -- a direction for a vocal or
instrumental part to be silent during a whole movement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

